reviews.review: I thought it was a good ending, however I wished that they had included the significant characters at the end that were also Jedi. I hope the franchise continues with Rey forming and training new Jedi.
JJ Abrams .... amazing.  Now come back to Star Trek!
Movie completes the Star War story. Well made, keeps you guessing. Great action and visual effects. Recommend you see in theatre with quality sound system and big screen.

Was given some free tickets from a radio station giveaway. I didn't have high expectations from the start having seen what Disney and Rian Johnson did to the previous movies. This served me well as I found the Rise of Skywalker to be quite disappointing in terms of storyline, consistency and its ability to explain itself within the Star Wars universe and its link to Canon.

Thankfully I didn't waste any of my own money to watch this movie, though it sadly is time that I'll never get back.

This is a real disappointing ending to watch could've been a great trilogy of movies had Disney not destroyed it and for that I blame George Lucas for selling the rights without condition.

Rise of Skywalker uses nostalgia and a broom with a dustpan to be rid of the last jedis misdeeds. All the while introducing new characters for the 3rd movie in a row whose names you'll forget 4 seconds once they're off screen. One story arc on particular does stand out and felt real and believable; while another character continues to have no flaws, problems, or hero's journey. The scenery and atmosphere continue to amaze in certain moments but is drowned out by a forgetful 2 hour scavenger hunt. Most 5 star reviews seem to be fans that don't want to be honest that this trilogy will be forgotten and not count as canon star wars films in the years to come.
it's a fun movie but it could be better because the script is not well developed
Feels like what should’ve been of episode 8 and 9, smashed into one. Given proper time both in production and on screen and this would’ve been good!
Fantastic!   The perfect way to tie up the entire 9 movie series.

While nothing beats the original three movies, this last installment is the best of the newer six films. It uses nostalgia from the original movies but also gives a satisfactory conclusion. Kudos for the Carrie Fisher work this was an impossible situation that they did their best with.
